### TITLE ###
Confirm yes via enter
### DESCRIPTION ###
confirm() is a text field interpreted as yes/no: an empty answer (just Enter)
defaults to yes.
### INPUT ###
print(confirm())
### KEYS ###
enter
### STDOUT ###
true

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > █
--- frame 1 (enter) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > 
### TITLE ###
Confirm yes via y
### DESCRIPTION ###
Any answer starting with 'y' (case-insensitive) counts as yes.
### INPUT ###
print(confirm())
### KEYS ###
"y"
enter
### STDOUT ###
true

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > █
--- frame 1 (y) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > y█
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > y
### TITLE ###
Confirm no via n
### DESCRIPTION ###
An answer that does not start with 'y' counts as no.
### INPUT ###
print(confirm())
### KEYS ###
"n"
enter
### STDOUT ###
false

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > █
--- frame 1 (n) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > n█
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > n
### TITLE ###
Confirm cancel
### DESCRIPTION ###
Ctrl-C aborts the prompt, surfacing as a rad error and a non-zero exit.
### INPUT ###
print(confirm())
### KEYS ###
ctrl-c
### STDERR ###
error[RAD20010]: Error reading input: input canceled
  --> <script>:1:7
  |
1 | print(confirm())
  |       ^^^^^^^^^
  |
   = info: rad explain RAD20010


### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Confirm? [Y/n] > █
### EXIT ###
1
